{
  "texts": [
    "We will comment later on the equivalence of these two proofs, and will indeed use the equivalence for the final step.",
    "27 Aside from the final step, this derivation of the localisation will be more succinct than the literature.",
    "It also directly writes the covering map formula in terms of AdS 3 coordinates, namely γ(z) = e -Σ(z) from the Wakimoto representation, rather than the coordinates of its twistor space ξ ± (z).",
    "For different reasons, it has been suggested before in [4,14] that inserting the Wakimoto coordinate γ(z) should lead to the covering map, but this was only verified up to first sub-leading order.Let's first analyse the OPE structure of e -Σ.",
    "It is a simple exercise to show that e -xJ + 0 e -Σ e xJ + 0 = e -Σ + x.This allows us to compute the OPE with twisted sector ground states ase -Σ(z) V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i) = e x i J + 0 (e -Σ(z) + x i) V w i m i 1,m i 2 (0; z i)e -x i J + 0 = x i V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i) + (z -z i) w i e x i J + 0 exp -Σ(z) + f w i m i 1,m i 2 (z i) e -x i J + 0 = x i V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i) + (z -z i) w i V w i m i 1 -1/2,m i 2 -1/2 (x i; z i) + O((z -z i) w i +1), (4.4)where we use the formula (3.10) and we see that our intuition for (4.3) was correct."
